hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Let me start off with saying this was the worst hotel I have stayed at in a long time. While in France my friend and I stayed at many hotels as we traveled around and enjoyed them all with the exception of this one. There are no "5-star" aspects to this hotel - I have no idea how it can even be called that.
From the moment we arrived it was off to a bad start. There is no door man or person to help with bags (also something I have never seen at a 5-star hotel). They also lock their front door and it can only be opened with a key (24hrs a day). We arrived at around 1:30pm for check in and after dragging our own bags out of our car we forced to wait at the door for a guest to come out in order to get into the hotel (keep in mind it was raining). We went to check in and the experience was bizarre. Not one thing about the hotel was told to us and a key was handed over. We went up to our room to find out there was no water whatsoever running (something that should have been told to us upon arrival). The room was also not as pictured - it was tacky, dated and looked like a child had been jumping on our bed and furniture in the room. We went out for the day hoping the water would be resolved. Upon our return we were told the water was working again. We went to our room to find it working (yay) but ONLY at scalding not. To the point we had to wash our faces by wetting a cloth, letting it dry and then using it 5 min later. We were unable to even shower. And our toilet would not flush.
Fast forward to going to sleep after a day of exploring and a green light on our wall was SO bright it eliminated the entire room - thankfully the next night we covered it with items of clothing and face masks in order to dull the light but again not something you'd ever expect to have to do at a "5-star" hotel. The staff was not friendly or helpful at all and made their lack of interest well known.
I could go on and on as we hated our experience that much but will wrap by saying do not stay here. There are MANY gorgeous hotels for a fraction of the price in Paris and this was a huge miss. Definite pass for us.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Staying at this hotel was a huge regret! Most of my things were stolen from my hotel room, and when we raised the issue to the hotel staff they were uncooperative, rude, and offered no help whatsoever, in fact they have actually decided not do anything about the stolen items even though it was stolen from my locked hotel room. They wouldn’t even show us the security cameras footage to help. Worst experience ever! If you’re considering on staying here, DON’T! You will be a victim of theft in this place.

Safety -2/10
Service -5/10

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: This hotel ruined my whole trip, I have never experienced a situation like this before. I was really disappointed by how they reacted toward my problem which was a theft that happened within the hotel. I have placed the do not disturb sign and regardless of it they entered the room organized and cleaned it and STOLE two bags with expensive items in it. When I asked them for their help they didn’t show any interest and were totally unbothered by my complaints. When I told them what happened they started denying my words with no proof and tried to convince me that I left my belongings somewhere else, which is more frustrating than the whole situation. As a person who payed and stayed in this hotel I expected more from them but unfortunately I was really disappointed by their manners and communication this is a horrible place with a horrible staff that made me feel worse by asking for their help to find who entered the room while I was out. My advice is to never stay here because they do not deserve your trust even though they placed card of access for entry and make you feel they care about your safety, THEY DONT.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We paid for the premium room, some of which have a balcony, I emailed a week ahead of time to request a balcony which they said is not guaranteed, and upon arrival they said they never recieved this email. Upon arrival, the couple that checked in at the same as us received a balcony room, we did not, even though we paid for an upgraded room and requested in advance. Furthermore, one of the front desk staff jumped into the conversation and began to raise his voice at me which was very rude. They said they will try for the next day, but when I called they said no one ever reserved that specific room to chnage us so someone else got it. How hard is to see when someone with that room checks out and move us there. Point being: POOR COMMUNICATION AT THE FROMT DESK AND RUDE. Rooms are large and comfortable. No amenities. Basically you can pay less for an Air BnB. We are stil staying here so well see if it improves.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Fabulous!!! I visited with my mother and my two daughters for a long weekend. Perfect location, short walk to Eiffel Tower, amazing shops, cafes, restaurants nearby. Supermarket a few doors up for essentials and a pharmacy, also Carrefour over the road. Room perfect, we had a deluxe 2bed apartment, 100% cleaning standards, linen changed daily.. immaculate, could not fault cleanliness/hygiene at all.

Only small negative thing to mention is that they leave some lovely L’occitane products in the rooms, nice that they replace them so much, keeping shampoos etc topped up but I used a lovely bar of verbena soap and it was replaced each day, bit of a waste, only used it for handwashing, I left it by sink each morning…came back later each day to find a new one in wrapper, so they were obviously being binned and replaced, a bar would of lasted months so just one for the whole 4 days would have been fine!

Brilliant gym! Beautiful decor and art, free coffee machine in lobby, nice cappuccinos! Staff very friendly and helpful, excellent English!
Close to Metro stations although we mostly walked and used Uber.
Wasn’t bothered by any noise at all, was on 5th floor, busy street below but was so tired each night, didn’t hear anything at all!
Room had iron/ironing board, hairdryer, a safe, coffee machine, all kitchen utensils, pans etc to cook a meal, microwave, dishwasher, oven/hob…

Would highly recommend and stay again definitely, the hotel made our trip to Paris even more magical. 5 stars well deserved, Thankyou.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: My wife and I had a great experience at this hotel thanks to Thiago. Great location, within steps of the Eiffel Tower. Everyone at the front desk was helpful and polite. We enjoyed our stay here. Would definitely stay there again.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
So you thought you found a very nice, chic hotel, high end, best location at a super price? well, you didn't. If you want to pay good location and high end, go to the Peninsula up the street.
If you want to pay high and have a terrible experience, gross, old room, bad service, expensive mediocre breakfast...stay here.

I fell for the nice photos in the website, the name of the hotel and the fact that they had "laundry" for my family stay.
WELL, wrong worst decision. there are 2 Laundry rooms in the whole hotel which don't work, so don't stay for this feature. The rooms, the amenities, the towels, the odor... what's up tin this apart-hotel. And in the front desk they don't want to help. because THEY CHARGE YOU UPFRONT the first day. So, you're a captive costumer.

just don't fall for it! believe me.
Even if it has a very good location, Paris has many more very good location rooms! "its not the last coke in the desert"

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: As I lay here, at 2 am, with white noise and headphones, unable to get away from the erratic base beat of the bar below us, I wonder at the wisdom of a hotel who would do that to a guest who reserved 3 weeks in advance and arrived at 6 pm. The hotel itself is a fine location, and the other room we were given was roomy and quiet. But then this. Beware the dreaded room 133. If you’re given that room and the hotel is booked, guess what? Its an apology note with a box of jelly candies plus 2 sleepless nights for you.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: With fantastic features, remarkable attention to details and ultimate luxury, the Hotel is one of the best in Paris. Between Trocadero and Avenue des Champs Elysées, the hotel’s location is strategic, as it allows for a very easy access to other important landmarks such as Palais de Chaillot, the Arc de Triomphe, and the iconic avenues that derive from Place de l’Étoile. Pallais Galliera renowned for its fashion exhibitions, Musée d’Art Moderne and Palais de Tokyo. Cherry on the cake, the gorgeous Suite Tour Eiffel offers an incomparable view of its namesake monument.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
;-) great location close to Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe
Front d’est team very helpful
A special thanks to Roberto
Family room can easily welcome a family of 5 with a smal kitchen corner
Grocery store located at 100 m
A lot of restaurants nearby
A great breakfast with no much choice but dedicated F&B team

:-( housekeeping to be improved
We waited 3 hours before getting our room which was meant to be free

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Great location, we could not ask for more coz of my personal preference to be accessible to Tour Eiffel by only few minutes walk.

The warm and professional welcome provided by young professionals, Ms Attitaya at the front desk and Mr. Louis Villeroy. Much appreciated!

Room itself is located on 6th floor, with lovely balcony.

Pros: Spacious, well better than what we could expect from Paris. Well equipped, L'Occitane amenities and clean.

Cons: Bed is comfy but pretty small, many holes detected on the sheer curtains, only one bottle of water provided on arrival, but not on second day. And the noise disturbance from the corridor both day and night.

Breakfast: Good variety of food offerings, with quality. Station for the hot drinks is not really my cup of tea, in particular at the 5-starred property. Should be more to be made by order, including eggs offerings for ex. But lovely services provided by both gentlemen. Thank you

Property to be highly recommened!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Stayed here for 4 nights with my wife last month. The room itself was great and the location is fantastic, with the Eiffel Tower less than 10 minutes one way and the heart of the Champs Elysees barely 15 mins the other. The hotel gym is also well equipped. However this is just not a 5 star property and disappointed in so many ways:

- there is no bar or restaurant onsite, not even a vending machine. There is no mini bar in the room or even any biscuits, just a minimal selection of coffees. I would find this poor for a 3* hotel let alone 5*

- the service is just average - it isn't awful, some people are helpful, others less so but, in British hotel terms, it's no better than a Travelodge. Service from head office is no better.

- a few days before arrival I had an email asking for special requests- we made a couple, they were ignored and there seems to be no record they were even asked for

- the suite we chose was advertised in images as having a balcony- not a huge one but big enough to sit on and have breakfast. It did not - the first had none and the second a 'standing room only' type arrangement with barely room for a chair.

All told, would certainly not recommend to anyone looking for anything like a 5* hotel which is a shame given the location.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
We stay 4 nights in the hotel. Everything was very nice. Because of Covid situation some service are not availabe but the frendly staff informed us nicely about everything.
The position of the hotel is excellent…
The room are clean and tidy…
We were on the room no.632

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
I stayed two night at this property in room 717 which is a top floor room.
Great view over Paris rooftops and Montmartre. Very quiet and private. Well appointed room with coffee machine, fridge, crokery, mico wave. Large bathroom with a separate shower and a bathtup.
Staff is both freindly and professional. Fantastic location on avenue Kleber. Safe area setps away from Palais de Chaillot which offers a fantastic view of the Eiffel tower. Great property for business travellers.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Me and my wife stayed here to celebrate my 50th birthday. Upon arrival we were seen by Tina who was brilliant. We were upgraded to a room with a view of the Eiffel Tower, complimentary champagne and sweets with a note from hotel management to celebrate my birthday.
Rooms and hotel was immaculate and clean. Lovely breakfast. Super location made it easy for sightseeing.
Thanks La Clef for making our trip to Paris a wonderful and memorable experience.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Spacious rooms and good location but the housekeeping service can be better and must be enhanced . Also, there was no in room dining which I feel now it’s a necessity in all hotels . The staff are friendly .

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Beautiful room and layout for families. It has two bedrooms, two bathrooms, kitchenette, dishwasher, fridge and washing machine. Amazing fitness center! Great amenities and service. Very close to major attractions, shopping and restaurants.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Amazing staff who are friendly and very helpful. The location is perfect, just steps to many restaurants, shops and of course the Eiffel Tower. The hotel itself is well maintained and stylish. I would absolutely go back.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
The hotel itself is in a beautiful building just few meters from the Trocadero square and the Eiffel tower itself. Hotel has very nice lobby and breakfast room and has very well equipped gym and even a steam room (which I did not use). Rooms are a bit outdated and the furniture is worn out, but overall in solid condition.

However, the glass in the room was dirty two days in a row (I had to clean them myself) and I have found long black hair in my bathroom two times on two different days - one in the towel and another in the tub. Mind you, I am male with short brown hair.

In addition to that, knowing that I will be in a hurry the morning of departure I kindly asked the reception agent to pay for the room and to give him my company details for the invoice. He politely collected my payment and the details and clearly told me that my invoice will be waiting in the morning. Long story short, I was waiting for full 15 minutes while young lady at the reception was fidgeting and trying to find existing one or issue a new invoice, all without any success. I have lost my prebooked ride for the airport and in the end got my receipt by mail few hours later.

To conclude, I can tolerate lots of things in a hotel, but absence of basic hygiene cannot and will not.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
We were on an anniversary celebration trip and this was our last of three hotels. We had stayed at La Clef Louvre a week earlier (which was wonderful) so our hopes were high....

Unfortunately, this was a bit of a disappointment. Upon arrival, they didn't have our room ready - that's ok, we were actually a little early. Then, check in hour arrived and the room still wasn't ready.... we waited....and waited. We were eventually checked in to a room 30-40 minutes after the guarancteed check in, we were given a key to our room. I had questions about the room I was being assigned. I reviewed my reservation and was reasonably certain that the room assigned was not the room I paid (extra) for. Now, the room was quite nice - well appointed and recently updated. It was not, however, what I paid for.

I went to the front desk - to no avail. I called my travel agent. They couldn't get through to the hotel. I went back to the front desk...the manager was too busy to see me. EVENTUALLY, the assistant manager called me and invited me to come down. She offered a room upgrade to a one bedroom suite - in a part of the hotel that had not been renovated. It was a lovely, if dated room that also smelled a bit like it hadn't been used in some time. We enjoyed the room and all in all in was quite acceptable - if dated.

Unfortunately, the service (with the exception of the Assistant manager) never really improved and service is what actually makes a 5 star hotel a 5 star hotel.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
First of all thank you for the prefect staff the pleasant stay, for the kind assistance of Morgan but all the other staff are just professional and kind!!!
The location is perfect, steps away from Trocadero, nice locals around, everything you need. The rooms are big and furnished very contemporary, comfortable. Also acceptable the price-performance ratio.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Our family of five thoroughly enjoyed our stay at this hotel. Hotel was lovely and unlimited access to the coffee machines was a nice extra. The hotel is in a fabulous location for the Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: La Cleff Tour Eiffel is a classy hotel, great size room - fairly big for one person and big bathroom. Facilities available within the room are great, such as microwave and fridge. Walls are extremely thin so you will get woken up by lifts and noises in the corridor, particularly from housekeeping. Otherwise cleaning service is good, and the hotel is very safe. Great location for sightseeing! Lots of nice cafes and restaurants nearby. Not much in-room dining options available, and slightly overpriced for what it's worth.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Overall, I was happy with the customer service rendered to us as I found the staff at La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris to be friendly and would go an extra mile to ensure that one had a good stay with them. They also assisted in calling us cabs/taxis to take us to wherever we needed to go.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
General: I stayed at La Clef Tour Eiffel for 7 nights with my husband and we had booked the Classic Double room without breakfast. We didn’t have any view of the Eiffel Tower, which honestly we thought we would (perhaps we had to request it beforehand, I’m not exactly sure).

Check-in and check-out: Check-in was done rather smoothly and the gentlemen at the front desk was extremely accommodating and quick to get us into our room. Check-out was also very hassle-free, we just payed for the extra breakfast we had eaten during our stay and we were in our way.

Room: The room was extremely well put together, with a nice modern touch and finishing, button controlled curtains, a Nespresso machine, boiler, a TV and a fantastic bathroom. Overall the room had all the facilities you could need during your stay from an iron, to good closet space, WiFi, and most importantly (for me at least) - a good heating and cooling system. The only comment I have about the room is that it lacked electric sockets as well as lighting. There was only two side lamps next to the bed for lighting and only 1 extra socket we could use to charge our personal devices. House keeping did a decent job at keeping the room clean, they replaced most of the toiletries (except for the bath bar) and for some reason we never got a “turn-down” service experience. Other than that the room was always left in excellent condition.

Location: In terms of location the hotel was located in a fantastic neighborhood. It took roughly 20 minutes to walk to the Paris hotspots such as the Champs Elysees, the Eiffel Tower and the Arc De Triomphe. There were also plenty of cozy bakeries only 1 minute away from the hotel which made the most delicious croissants and also had decent breakfast options. Something else which we found very convenient was a close supermarket which we went to to buy any items we needed during our trip. The location although in a prime spot was not noisy and we never felt disturbed from the area or the outdoors.

Food: In terms of food, the options were pretty limited in the hotel. The in-room dining did not have many options and we were better off having lunch and dinner in the many restaurants of Paris. The breakfast was on the pricier side (25 Euros per person) and it mostly had continental options. The breakfast was decent and convenient but definitely not worth the price so we chose to dine out most of the time. They also offered complimentary tea and coffee in the afternoon.

General: In general we really enjoyed our stay at the Le Clef Tour Eiffel and we would definitely return to it on our next trip to Paris. The hotel was comfortable to stay in, very safe as well (you couldn’t physically enter the hotel without your room key which we found extra comforting). In addition, it had good facilities overall.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
As you can see from reading all my reviews, I travel a lot and stay at 4 or 5 star hotels and for good reason. This hotel states 4 star service, yet it is far from it. When you walk in to check in, you will be greeted and checked in and then no one will ever reach out to you nor check in with you to see how your stay is. I mean we would walk past the staff daily 5-6 times a day when going out, and they never raised their heads off their phones and laptops to even say HI.... The rooms were fine, nothing over the top. I have to let everyone know to stay away from this hotel.... You will pay top $ but in return get a basic bed, pillow and maid service I paid $900 USD a night and the Courtyard down the street would give me better service. It is clear that this place only has one concern $$$ no customer service at all, they made us feel as if were a bother being there. When we finally checked out, I finally had someone say one thing to me.... " Your final bill is"
My fellow reviewers, we have to trust each others reviews and I am doing my part telling you to look for somewhere else! I have lots of people message me for more info so feel free.

Thank You
David

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Location is good but don’t be fooled, you can’t see the tower from your room as advertised. Service was excellent, rooms clean and spacious. Will definitely recommend this establishment. The rooms are equipped with a microwave and large fridge.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris was a very beautiful hotel. Customer service was excellent. The location was perfect. Very clean, comfy and cozy. Very impressive. I would definitely stay here if in Paris again. Thank you.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Location and walkability are perfect. Staff is very friendly and accommodating. Rooms are very nice and clean and the bed and pillows are comfortable. Our room was nice and quite. Close to many attractions and conveniences. Will stay here again without hesitation.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Great location and excellent service, room are not new but really clean and well maitained, bathtub is very comfoable, I use bathtub more because water leaks from the shower to the floor at room 727 which is ok.
Hotel between Arc De triophe and Eiffel Tower, about 18 min walking to Champ Elysees.
Outside of the hotel is a MINI mart has everything..
Overall nice hotel and French people are nice and open minded, but Paris is really bad, thiefs every where who normally targets on tourists and greedy useless council people and police. Only place worth to go is Louvre museum or shopping, Chanel, LV and PP is cheaper.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Beautiful hotel. Location is perfect. You can walk up the street and have the best view of the Tower in the whole city. You can walk to the Tower in 5 minutes, if that.

Very elegant, clean and professional staff. This was my 2nd time staying there. I brought my mother there for her birthday in December 2018. They made a mistake in our room reservation and comp'd us a weekend visit in an upgraded room for the inconvenience. The manager, Ms. Anita Steinman is one of the best hotel managers I've come across.

If you're looking for a super elegant feel and stay, this is the place.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
My significant other and I thoroughly enjoyed our stay at this hotel. The hotel was in a great location, walking distance to see the Eiffel Tower, next to a monop' (convenience store) and close to public transportation (both the metro and if you want to take Le Bus Direct to CDG or Orly). Upon arrival, we had a swift check in process and were given a tour of the facilities. The staff was also helpful with answering all of our inquiries.

We were impressed by how spacious the room was as well as the wifi speed. The bathroom was also super nice, as it has "his and her" sinks and the toilet is separate from the shower area. The cleaning service was great too - we always had fresh towels and they offered a turn down service nightly.

In addition, we absolutely loved the facilities here- the gym was well stocked with equipment and the hotel offered tea time with free juices and pastries. Our only complaint was the quality and contents of the breakfast - as there are very few options for the amount that you are paying. Overall, we had a great time at this location!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Having visited Paris before we decided to choose a different location and this hotel is well situated in the Trocadero area close to the Eiffel Tower. Great location for many of the tourist hot spots.
The hotel was beautifully presented and the staff extremely helpful and attentive. However, the hotel just felt a little soulless with a real lack of any vibe and atmosphere. If you are looking for a quality hotel which is clean, elegant and quiet then look no further. On the other hand if you are looking for a hotel with a vibe and the buzz of a usual big city hotels then you will not experience this here.
From an Englishman's viewpoint wanting my morning cup of tea, this was not a great option. Only 4 tea bags for 2 people and not one that wasn't aromatic or fruity

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Thank you to god angel Bernavie for making our stay a dream come true. We renewed our wedding vows while our week stay in Paris. Bernavie from the moment we checked it which was at 9:30am made it special even though our room wasn’t ready. When she found out we were celebrating a vow renewal Bernavie went above and beyond to make that day super big and special the next day. Allow us the Eiffel Tower Suite for the day, since it was super cold and raining that day. After almost a year of chemo and yes I was very sick during our trip. She help my husband give me a trip to remember. Our room was amazing, we had stair going down to the full tub and shower was great. Our room was clean and very spacious. Everyone from the night chief (which I often was hurry at 1:30 am) maybe amazing food. Tea and coffee where in the room and in the hotel lobby. The hotel location was great, close to metro and all major landmarks. The restaurant around the hotel were also great. Our personal favor was Mokus. Everyone was so friendly, spoke all three languages. France, English and Spanish.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Our stay was less then good, we encountered many issues while we were there. We traveled a far distance, had our previous accommodations cancelled at the last minute (through booking.com) and booked the property at their suggestions. It was a bit rocky from the minute we arrived, the Front desk was clearly overwhelmed...while checking in our agent was interrupted no less than 5 times while trying to check us in. Once we got our keys, went to rooms, we were right away less than pleased as our room smelled like mildew. Here is a list of the other issues we encountered:
Had mold in bathrooms (in cracks of tile)
Vanity falling apart (loose piece of wood and mold exposed)
Leak from ceiling ( from light fixture) and bubbled paint and mold from leak site
Dryer did work, had someone come to room, could not get working. Had to ask for items to be dried elsewhere, they were returned back to the room and were still damp. I had to fly home with damp clothes ( 12 hours) and now my clothes were moldy too.
Next door to a club, so loud music ( with too much base) playing until 2am+
Again we were looking forward to this trip and have been planning and saving for quite some time. We would never stay here again, will not recommend to friends and family.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We loved this sophisticated hotel for its location and really friendly staff. They also have a really flexible approach. We would highly recommend this hotel. Excellent value for money given the location.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
We were checked in one hour late in wrong room. When we argued for 30 min then staff moved us in right room. Breakfast is not worth spending Euro 24 as they have eggs and sausages only.

The only good thing about the hotel in the location.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: This hotel was perfect for us. The location was Conviently located, walking distance to Effiel tower and restaurants. There's a nice market right next door carries everthing you need & want. Hotel front desk lady Lenora was very helpful & courteous. Very nice Classic room, very private section of hotel,clean and spacious!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Very nice hotel in super convenient location. We spent few days there with wife and children for my birthday and had a lovely apartment room with plenty of space a and nice view. A lot of "to do things" are just walking distance and there a good food options in the neighborhood.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Absolutely fantastic stay in Paris after 3 bad experiences in other hotels thanks to La Clef Tour Eiffel. Right at the beginning we got a free upgrade of rooms to Tour Eiffel Suite. The broken refrigerator was replaced within 2 hours. Very helpful service, hot air conditioning, priceless view, great gym and excellent breakfast. For excursions around Paris fantastic location on the Metro. Next year we return for an even longer stay.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Our rooms were not ready so we waited for 6 hours 2 hours past 3 pm check in. We were tired having taken an early morning flight and wanted at least luggage accommodations. Then we had to check with reception for our rooms and were told they would call when ready but they never did. We were not advised when our rooms were ready. They were not accommodating we were not offered food or water. We waited and waited. They were rude and did not help with our luggage. Rooms were okay but not fancy. Hotel location good but did not help to be treated so rudely and have waisted so much time. Overall I will never stay here a total disappointment

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We had an excellent stay at the La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris. The check in process was easy, the staff was welcoming, and our room was clean and cold after a long hot walk from the train station. The linens were not super soft, but the bed was high quality, as were the pillows.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: I just returned from a 5 night stay with my daughters and mother, and it was an exceptional hotel and experience in a perfect location of Paris. Beautifully decorated 1 Bedroom Executive Apartment with floor to ceiling windows and balconettes, a fully functioning kitchenette, very spacious, great air conditioning, comfortable, city views, excellent service and house keeping, extremely clean hotel, loved the breakfast buffet, easy check in and check out and we felt very safe. I am so glad we chose La Clef Tour Eiffel Our experience was absolutely wonderful and I highly recommend this hotel.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
What a beautiful hotel in a prime location of Paris. We stayed for 5 nights in a 1 Bedroom Executive Apartment and it was absolutely wonderful, modern and elegant style, including kitchenette and floor to ceiling windows with balconets, great air conditioning, extremely clean, spacious and excellent service from concierge to house keeping, the staff was amazing and always helpful, nice breakfast buffet. I highly recommend La Clef Tour Eiffel.
I would definitely return to this fine establishment.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: The room was nice, but attitude and courtesy of reception staff was negative and very unwelcoming, if not positively rude. Asking for directions we were met with derision and contempt. Upon check in we were told that the room was not ready at 3:25 pm. On the contrary on check out we were practically chased out of the room immediately; 5 past the hour, with intimidating staff knocking at the door. Not the best experience. Staff needs training in particular in cultural sensitivity.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
My husband and I are very impressed with this hotel. It’s in a fantastic location, just a stone’s throw from the Palais Chaillot, where there is the best view of the Eiffel Tower, only 500 m away.
The washing machine in our one-bedroom apartment is a bonus - so helpful when travelling - and there are French doors with Juliet balconies.
The staff are helpful, in that laissez-faire French way, and the facilities are great.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We spend 6 days at the hotel, the room with 2 rooms, living room and 2 Bathrooms. It was perfect for thouse who travel with kids. The location is perfect. The Eiffel Tower is just 1 block away, the Metro , Bus and Airport Bus is just at the corner. And you have 20 mt a little shop to buy all the groceries you need.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Location, location, location Great location
A wonderful place to stay, The staff were extremely nice and friendly
The Rooms were large and comfortable, Ticked all the boxes without being pretentious and over rated. Well done

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: A reliable place to stay in Paris while visiting. You are close enough to all the main areas of the city by tube or walk. Service was good and the people were very helpful during our stay. Would expect breakfast to be inclusive at this price point.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: My husband and I were in Paris celebrating our 20th wedding anniversary. This hotel was perfectly located and the service was wonderful. The management left us a bottle of champagne and a box of cookies to help us celebrate. We could not have asked for a better location. Having a mini-fridge in the room was also helpful. There is a monoprix right down the street to buy food. It helped that they do not keep the minibar stocked unless you request it, so there was plenty of room for things we bought. We were very impressed with this hotel. The only change we wished for was the length of the glass partition on the shower. It is not long enough to keep water off the floor. It wasn’t emerald an issue, though, more just an inconvenience, and one that is actually pretty common in France.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: I really wish I did not have to leave this review for this hotel... Especially while I am still checked in and staying here. In the past two weeks we have gone do Mykonos, Santorini, Athens and Barcelona for our honeymoon. Paris was supposed to be the crown-jewel of our honeymoon trip. We went about using this hotel due to its proximity to the Eiffel Tower and we booked it well in advance. We had specified wanting a view of the Eiffel Tower and when we would be checking in. The moment we checked-in is exactly when things started going downhill: Of course they couldn't accommodate our room request even though we had made it very well in advance. We ended up with a view overlooking a courtyard in the middle of the hotel--Which is to say, there was absolutely no view. We soon found out that the air conditioning in the room was stuck in the on position and the room heater did not work. Subsequently, throughout our stay, the room was frozen. No heat whatsoever. Then on our first night we had yet another problem: the shower. When my better half took a shower the entire bathroom became a lake. This is not an exaggeration to make a bad review sound worse. This is exactly what happened. I wasn't paying attention while she was showering. The moment she got out she let me know that the bathroom was literally flooded. We both thought it was something that she did maybe in leaving the shower door open?? After we used all the towelss we had and called for more I then decided to take a shower myself. It turns out there was a design problem with this particular shower and there is nothing you could do to prevent the bathroom from flooding because there is no lip or seal on the shower door. Downstairs we went to let the front desk know that the room was freezing, didn't have the view we had requested and that the bathroom was flooded. Nothing they could do about the view...Air conditioning: it was too late in the evening and they would try to have somebody come by the next day. Flooding in the shower: they said that they were aware of that particular problem with our specific shower and offered to give us more towels. ...Here we are on the third day and nobody has called to ask us about any of the problems we had or to see if we wanted to be moved to another room. So sad because this hotel demands a premium price and we have gotten something much less than a premium experience. We weren't informed, until we got to the hotel, that there would be a €35, per day charge for parking our car. Again it is a premium hotel so one wouldn't think that we would receive such a substantial charge for parking a car overnight. It all comes down to what we have spent for this hotel and given the level of service we have received, or lack thereof, it is extremely disappointing

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Specially located near L’Arc de Triomphe on one side and near the Tour Eiffel on the other - could not as for more!

Well maintained, ample rooms and good service. Good in room amenities. Worth evaluating for a special occasion.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
The room we stayed in was very spacious, service was excellent, breakfast very enjoyable and the location (just next to Trocadero) perfect.
I would highly recommend staying there for a (long) weekend in Paris.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
I spent 3 days at this amazing place on my first visit to France. The staff are so professional & helpful, the location is perfect as it's walking distance to the Eiffel tower, train station and so many other recreational places.

The accommodation was also cosy & spacious with amenities.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: My first time in Paris, I was with my daughter and son. When I arrived the doorman immediately took my bags and I checked in. The lobby is very nice, the representatives checked me in quickly. They were very nice and professional. While I waited for my room, I was offered refreshments which was very good, my room was beautiful. We had a full kitchen where we could fix a meal if we wanted. We were very close to restaurants so we ate out. We walked a few feet and the Eiffel Tower was there. We took beautiful pictures. The Arc de Triomphe was down the street. I would highly recommend staying here.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: The hotel is in a good location, cosy, spacious rooms. Very poor breakfast, located in the loby, so you have to sit on sofas, that is not really comfortable for eating. Would recommend to eat breakfast in the city if you have extra time. Had some issues with the staff.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
It’s a dream place in Paris! Beyond the wonderful and luxurious rooms, the service is really great, we’ve been treated very well.
The hotel location is also the best in town.
Thank you for this great and unforgettable experience.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Outstanding place to stay. Very closed to the perfect spot for photos of the effiel tower. Also, many shop close by. The metro is also close by. The staff respect everyone there. One evening I put on sweats and a hoodie and went to The effiel tower, when I came back, I was struggling to find my entrance key the surprisingly the door guy recognized me and open the door for me. That meant a lot to me. The staff were outstanding and the maid was respectful too. I will stay here sgain!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: The location could not be beat, we were in walking distance of Eiffel Tower and the arc de triomphe. We stayed over the New Year and had a wonderful trip seeing all this beautiful city has to offer, however this hotel is just ok. I do not consider it a five star, however I would choose it again based on the fantastic location and we felt safe. The room was clean, but it could use a bit of updating. The shower leaks everywhere, and we had to request extra towels everyday to mop up the water. There was a bit of a strange smell in the hallway at times, smelled somewhat of sewage, and the windows had to be opened for a while to give us relief. I would say all of the front desk staff we spoke with were extremely helpful and friendly. I would give the hotel 3.5 stars. Location alone does make it worth the stay, but could benefit from some upgrades.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
We chose this hotel as it seemed to offer reasonable rates for modern decor and a superb location. It certainly delivered on this. It is within walking distance of most major attractions, Underground and great local restaurants.

The only thing that spoiled our stay was a poor design in the shower screen over the bath which meant that water would come streaming out over the side of the bath and on to the bathroom floor.

The staff made the only suggestion they could "Stuff some towels down the side to try and block it".

The self service bar was also a little useless as there was no chilled items available.

The good news is, there is a supermarket a few doors down where we were able to purchase some supplies and stock the fridge.

Overall it was a good stay in a clean, reasonable room and the location is a very big bonus.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We stayed at La Clef for my partners birthday. We were in Paris for just 2 nights and I had planned something special with the hotel beforehand. Upon arrival I realised that the hotel had not carried out any of our arrangements. This was very disappointing and I expressed this to the staff. Unfortunately the staff on duty that evening were very unhelpful and did little to reconcile the situation. The following day I raised my concerns to the Hotel Manager, Anita. Anita was very helpful and to compensate for the hotels error she upgraded us to the best suite called the Tour Eiffel Suite. She also provided champagne and cake for my partner with a personalised note which was also very much appreciated. Anita made the experience special and for that alone I have rated the hotel 4 stars.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Our room was supposed to be 30sqm but it was no more than 20sqm. This is my of a 4 star hotel than 5 star because it does not have the amenities you expect with 5 star. However, it does have a beautiful lobby.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: My parents stayed at the La Clef as part of their 50 wedding anniversary trip. The hotel not upgraded their room and gave them champagne to celebrate this milestone event in their lives but the staff also took such good care of them. My parents are almost 80 and the staff made sure that they didn’t have to carry anything heavy, gave special instructions to taxi drivers to carry their bags etc. The manager also came out to welcome them to the hotel. My parents were so thrilled with the wonderful hospitality and the beautiful room they were given. Thanks La Clef and Anita for their best stay ever!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: I stayed at La Clef for a romantic get away during New Years. It was our first time in Paris. The people that works on this hotel did all the effort in their power to help us have a memorable experience. The people in the front desk were really committed to service. But also they were really knowledgeable of the different things Paris has to offer, so suggestions were always on point. If you are looking for a hotel in Paris for you and your spouse look no further. This will be it.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
If the hotel were not located so near the eiffel tower, this would be a one star. I booked this hotel as it was advertised as a 5 star hotel. It was not. Far from it. The concierge was never at the desk. The suggestions for fine French dining were just whatever was down the street when we spoke to the front desk. However, the most disappointing thing about this hotel were the rooms.

We booked a studio suite and when we got to the room, it was awful. Tiny and laid out horribly. The windows were floor to ceiling and were rusted all the way around the metal trim. The view was nothing special and we looked to upgrade as soon as was possible. On the upside in this room, the mattress seemed to be brand new and very clean.

We were upgraded the next day, at a charge of course. The room itself was much nicer and the view overlooked the street which was much nicer. I believe it was a "one bedroom apartment." The mattress here was older and less clean. The ceiling lamp had a large cobweb on it that was never cleaned for the next 4 nights. There was distinct smell of sewage or something foul that was always somewhat present. The room, while more spacious, was old. The couch cushions had cigarette burns on them and were dirty. There was a key card needed to be put in and left to keep the power on, including the fridge, that the staff pulled out while we were out and about regardless of what we had in the fridge.

I was not at all impressed with this hotel. It was not a 5 star experience and it was certainly not worth the price. Stay somewhere nicer.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
This was my first stay at this hotel. It is rated as a 5 star hotel. Located in one of the best streets of Paris, which is literally 5 min walking distance from the Place Du Trocadero and 10 min away from the Arc De Triomphe and the Champs-Elysées. I had a car with me so the Hotel had a valet service which I find very convenient. The receptionist was very friendly and finalized my check-in process in a timely manner. When I arrived my room wasn’t ready, so I thought I would have something to eat while waiting, but the hotel had no restaurants! Which I found it a bit weird to not find a restaurant in a 5* hotel.

The room:

- The size is fine
- Clean
- Modern Furniture
- Wide screen TV
- Kitchenette with a Microwave and Fridge
(empty)
- King size bed (comfortable)
- Bath robes
- Slippers for men and women (nice)
- Ironing board and Iron
- Safety box
- Sewing kit
- Shoe polish
- Huge Bathroom
- Hair dryer

I had to order room service but was told that the restaurant next door was closed because of the strikes which I totally understand, but again they should have an in house restaurant, so they only had a small selection of food that I had to order from and when the food arrived I discovered that they only have microwaved canned food. So literally my soup and beef were in cans. But to be fair it wasn’t that bad.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
This hotel does itself a major disservice by calling itself 5 star. It is on par with 3 star. We were deciding between this and Shangri La, which is very close by. We stayed in Shangri La in Bangkok and it was amazing, truly 5 star. The rooms at La Clef were clean and very comfortable. The location is excellent and the price is reasonable. Please do not pay extra for breakfast unless your sole goal is early morning convenience. It's very average and you'll get better value dining out. Administration-wise, there seemed to be a lot of confusion. They somehow didn't have our reservation when we arrived, but fortunately had a room available. Not sure how that would've played out in the busy season though. Then checking out, rather than reviewing the room and then asking for any outstanding payment, they automatically were trying to charge for things that had already been settled.

We stayed in the two-room suite and it was nice. The living room had good appliances, a big fridge, glassware and some space to relax. The bedroom/bathroom had a very comfortable bed and nice dark curtains. Hot water was excellent, but no tub.
The location is right next to Monop, a small supermarket that had fresh vegetables, wine, beer (including some craft beer!), and pretty much anything else you'd need. Lots of restaurants in the area, and Trocadero M station was maybe 5 minute walk. Excellent viewing of the Eiffel tower is also a short walk away.

All in all, I would definitely recommend someone stay here, with the caveat not to expect 5 star. Oh, one more note about Paris in general- almost nothing is open before 9am and many things close at 5.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
This is not a 5 star hotel, as advertised. The hotel does not have adequate customer service. There is no proper concierge to provide insights to dining and other activities. There was a massive issue upon check out where the hotel incorrectly charged us $150 and they were not willing to waive or speak reasonably about the charge. Hotel is a good location off the Trocadero.

Would stay away at all costs and stay at the Sofitel one block away, instead

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We just returned from spending 6 nights at La Clef Tour Eiffel and I'm not sure there are enough words to express how much we enjoyed our stay there...the staff were so friendly and curtious...the afternoon tea is divine...the rooms were extremely large...it was quiet and clean...you can not top the location...to everything...great neighborhood...grocery store and pharmacy right next door...which had really good wine to purchase to bring back to our room...the room decor is stylish and beautiful

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
If wanting a great location (close to Eiffel Tower) then this is a very good option. Rooms are of a satisfactory standard, certainly not 5*.

Beds are small (King size) and not all rooms have bath tubs. Our shower didnt work well and water easily escaped from under the shower door making the rest of the bathroom wet. Surround lighting around mirror didnt work and nor did the safe.

This is more or an Apart-Hotel - the service you get isnt marvellous (although far from bad) - when ordering a hot drink to the room the first answer I received was "there is a kettle in your room"... I asked for Hot Chocolate, i received a packet of chocolate powder.

Breakfast at 25 euros, dont even bother - coffee from an old machine.

I had 3 rooms booked and also had 2 young children with me - i requested a late check out - wow, this was difficult and i knew via the GDS system it wasnt full, so could have been managed however appeared the end of the world to honour.

Would i recommend? if wanting good location for a business trip, yes... if leisure and wanting a service with a smile,absolutely not.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
My husband and I stayed at the Sofitel (100m up the road) for 5 nights and then moved across to Le Clef for 4 nights while in Paris. La Clef was so much better!

Upon arriving at La Clef we went through an efficient check in process and were allocated our deluxe room 104 (first floor). We unpacked and then went out for dinner. Upon arriving back to the room I could hear music. After a very quick inspection I ascertained that our room was situated immediately above the hotel's ground floor bar which turns into a disco in the evening. I'm a light sleeper so this was not ideal. I was so tired that I convinced myself I could sleep through it. But within 10 minutes the music ramped up and the doof doof from the base was very prevalent. My husband went to reception to address our issue. The staff member, without hesitation, escorted my husband to the 4th floor to show him 2 alternative rooms, but guided him immediately to the nicest of the 2 as his recommendation (from recollection, room 408). My husband then came and took me upstairs to ensure we would both be happy with the room swap. As it turned out, our room move was to a 1 bedroom executive apartment i.e. a kitchenette, lounge room with desk area, and with separate bedroom and ensuite. This wasn't a room move but an upgrade - a very nice one and most appreciated. The room was extremely comfortable and, more importantly, quiet. It was well serviced every day by housekeeping.

Breakfast was down on the ground floor with an excellent array of food and drink choices. We could not fault this hotel.

The quality of the hotel, rooms and staff were all excellent. Again, I would like to thank the staff who we spoke with on our first day for resolving our issue in such a professional and efficient manner. It was 5 star service.

Beyond this, the hotel location is fantastic. It's about 600m to the Eiffel tower and 800m to the Champs Elysees. We had a view of the Champs Elysees from our balcony. There were also 2 metro stops within 100m which were well used by us to get around Paris city.

I highly recommend this hotel.

We will definitely be back.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
La clef is close to the Eiffel Tower. That’s about the only thing that went right during our stay. Negative experience would be an understatement.
- Towels were dirty (brown stuff on white towel)
- first night when we found a maid in the hallway she said we could not exchange towels because cleaning staff was no longer there for the day.
- Shower had past guest hair on the wall and ground.
- tea time downstairs didn’t have cups or any condiments refilled.
- the toilet did not flush the toilet paper. They had sanitary bags to put your toilet paper in the trash but did not let us know if we should use those or just flush.
- the wall outlet blew out causing my girlfriends straightener to break.
- I booked 2 separate reservations with this hotel on accident (3 nights first) (1 night second) for a total of 4 nights and instead of telling me I would need to change my key after day 3 I found that out the hard way as my key was turned off. No problem if the line at the front desk didn’t take 20 minutes to complete current check in and get me a new key.
-No Bar or restaurant in hotel.
-No explanation of amenities of hotel.
- major let down in service

- overall hotel quality 6/10
- overall staff quality 3/10

Would I recommend or suggest. - NO! Stay somewhere else.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: La Clef is hidden behind a classic Parisian street front and opens into a bright spacious hotel. The rooms are large and very quiet. The hotel decor is elegant with surprising touches of charming art and lovely furniture. As others have mentioned it’s hard not to flood the bathroom when you shower due to inadequate shower screens but strategically placed towels wedged between the screen and the vanity solved the problems. Everything else was splendid. The staff were friendly and very helpful. The location is close to two metro lines and there are numerous cafes along kleber as well as a supermarket

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: This is a great place with a wonderful atmosphere with large clean rooms and lots of counter space in the bathroom! Our room had a kitchenette and laundromat. It’s location is near the metro in addition the Eiffel Tower is very close, cafe’s, grocery store and many other choices.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Our family took a short trip to Paris to celebrate wife's 50th birthday. Our 2 bedroom facing Ave Keibler was ready. It was as expected, clean, comfortable and well maintained. The staff is polite and accomodating. The location is super convenient, located near restaurants and the Eiffel Tower. This location is perfect for families with young children like myself as it is safe and relatively quiet as it is 10-15min away from the shopping area. I will give preference to this hotel chain when we travel to London next. The quality of the experience for my family was first rate. We look forward to staying with you again.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Location cannot be beat. Less than 5 min walk to have a view of the Eiffel Tower. Same distance to the most popular hop on hop off tours of the city. Great restaurants and cafes within walking distance. Pleasant staff that spoke excellent English. Clean and comfortable room. Only complaints are that the bathroom floor would become very wet with every shower and the wait time for the room during check in. I would definitely book this hotel on my next visit to Paris and have spoken highly of it to those who have asked about my visit.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Great location, between Eiffel Tower and Arc de Triomphe, ATM next door, excellent bakery down the street, American Pub across the street, liquor store a couple doors away, grocery store a couple of doors down, good cafes up and down the street. The room was good, enough room for the three of us, but nothing special. Service was good during our stay, everyone was very helpful. Safe and fun neighborhood. Great place to explore Paris.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We did a lot of research before choosing this hotel and it was the PERFECT choice. Everything is within walking distance from restaurants to the Seine river to the Eiffel tower. The hotel is stunningly beautiful, clean, spacious and the hospitality was wonderful. There is a quaint grocery store and pharmacy next door to this hotel for added convenience. We will absolutely stay here again!

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Just up the road from the Eiffel Tower, also the train station and buses at the front door. Nice clean room with a lovely bathroom. Fantastic gym with loads of equipment. Staff very friendly and helpful. Breakfast buffet small but fresh and tasty. Extremely close to many great cafes.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Great Hotel in fantastic location. Staff were very efficient and nothing was a problem. Would definitely stay again. The Hotel is location very near the Tub stations and walking distance to the Eiffel Tower

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
The hotel is in a fantastic location, central yet very quiet.
The staff went above and beyond to make us feel "special" during our mini-moon weekend.
Everything went smoothly, the room service breakfast was excellent and yet cheap.
Room was huge (exec. apartment), with all possible amenities inside.
A must-go for a nice Paris experience.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We stayed in La Clef Tour Eiffel for a few days as a business trip. Hotel's location is its main advantage, Staff are nice and helpful and rooms are reasonably clean. Overall, a nice place for stay. There is also free laundry facility for guests which comes very handy.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We stayed in an apartment on the 2nd floor and found it to be very very noisy due to a night club across the road. We were there 5 nights and wished we had asked to move earlier. We did move to the 5th floor on the final night. At $1,800 Aud per night, I would have hoped for a slightly better experience, however, the Fitness Centre made up for our concerns. The staff were helpful and the location is fantastic.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: What a great stay at this first class hotel/apartment next to the Eiffel Tower!! The best part is that we got this suite/apartment for 400 Euros a night. With a last minute reservation this was a great deal. The location was awesome because the Metro is a few steps away, and in Paris it's all about the Metro to get around.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
This was mine and my wife's first time in Paris and stayed here for a few nights. To begin, the staff is amazing, they were very eager to help and provide information on what to do and where to eat etc. I was so surprised on how close we were to the Eiffel Tower, it is literally steps away. The rooms are not that big but are nice. We ate breakfast at the hotel, which was decent, but had all of our meals at the surrounding cafes and restaurants.

We took the train from the Airport to the Hotel, and if you want my recommendation, DONT DO IT!!! It is quite difficult to be able to come off a long flight and haul all of your luggage on a train and take it up and down stairs and try to find a spot for you and your luggage to sit on a busy train. Just pay for an uber or a taxi which is around 45 Euros.

We will definitely be staying at this location again.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: i was very pleased to stay at your Hotel, perfect location, kind staff, quite rooms & the breakfast was excellent.My family were satisfied with their stay at La Clef, especially my children. Hope to visit again next year.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: If you are not worried about money stay here. It has great location, a feeling of luxury, not crowded and very polite and good service. Lots of nice places to eat and do shopping within walking distance.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: This hotel is fantastic. Nothing but good things to say. The front desk staff was friendly and helpful. The room was beautiful and the floors were amazing. The only thing was the shower water ended up on the floor, but everything else was wonderful. Clean hotel and nice area with plenty of good restaurants.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: I have traveled extensively and this was my first Delta Vacation. La Clef was one of the hotel choices and after researching, I chose this one. Upon arrival we were impressed with the exterior and interior appearance of the reception area. The staff was very friendly. We arrived at 7:30 am after traveling for 18 hours and our check in was scheduled for 3:30 pm. The desk said our room was available which was great as we were able to take a brief nap, freshen up, and enjoy the afternoon. It is only about a five minute walk to a plaza for a great view of the Eiffel Tower. The room and bathroom size was surprising as reasonable priced Paris hotel rooms are small. Will choose this hotel the next time I'm in Paris.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
This Hotel is really lovely. Its beautifully French on the outside with beautiful rooms.
We had a room that looked out over the front street (Kleber). They are a nice sized room. Comfy beds with good quality linen. The bathrooms are lovely. There is a free afternoon tea at 4pm (Nice touch). The check in staff are so helpful, from restaurant suggestions to taxi's, to sightseeing.. Every little thing was their pleasure. There are a large number of restaurants in close walking distance. At the end of the street there are restaurants with views of the Eiffel Tower. At the other end there is the Arc.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Excellent location - so close to Eiffel Tour and other main attractions like Arc we Triomphe and Champ de Elysses shopping street, spacious and very comfortable rooms, staff are super friendly and helpful, highly recommended

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Ideally located obviously to the Eiffel Tower but could walk to most places that you wanted to see. Metro station across the road and very easy to work out the metro system.
Hotel room was spacious enough with a nice bathroom.
Stay were very good and would do anything for you.
Afternoon tea spread each day was a nice touch.
I would recommend.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Very nice feel at home hotel with large rooms and very warm and helpful staf close to everything that Paria has to offer.

Good beds. Perhaps more drink bottled water in the room at these hot days would be a suggestion and some in the fridge?

Nice beds aswell😇🙏

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Stayed 4 fantastic days at this hotel. Good location, beautiful interior finishes. Clean environment. Loved the lounge area and enjoyed the high tea in the afternoon. We were there during the Bastille day weekend and World cup finals. We were so close to the action at the Eifell town and our hotel was conviniently located. Good value for money would recommend to others

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: We absolutely loved staying at La Clef Tour Eiffel. The Hotel was beautifully decorated and so close to the Eiffel Tower. The staff were always extremely helpful. I would definitely recommend staying here.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews:
Welcomed so warmly. Wow. We had 2 rooms , one a flatlet ( with lounge, kitchenette and all) and one a big and roomy double room on the fifth floor. Nothing was too much to ask. Very comfortable, very modern. Afternoon tea a lovely treat.

Off Arch de Triomf down Klebber Ave. easy access to Trocadero Metro with many upmarket restaurants around. A short walk to Champ Elysees and Eiffel Tower. And there is a small grocery store a few metres where one could buy fruit and out-to-home meals, tuck into microwave in-room. ....Did I mention the strong free wifi....

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: For those traveling to Paris with family, this hotel is beautifully situated. Neighborhood is nice and walking distance from tour Eiffel, champs elysees, arch de triumph and la Sine . Cafes nearby are nice. Hotel itself is clean and spacious and staff are friendly. Will go there again surly.

hotel: La Clef Tour Eiffel Paris by The Crest Collection
reviews: Quite liked this place. Rooms were lovely. It has a suite with 2 bedrooms which is suitable for families. It provided nice toiletries. Place is near Cafe Jamin, a restaurant I'd recommend. Check in was a bit slow though.
